## Overview

This workspace contains data-centric Postman collections and requests for accessing and utilizing open data from **[{{ name }}]({{ home }})**. It features user-friendly APIs connecting to a diverse array of datasets, selected for their popularity and relevance, covering topics such as transportation, public safety, environment, and housing.

## Data Centric Collections

Unlike traditional Postman collections that focus on APIs, data-centric collections are organized around specific datasets or data sources. Their documentation emphasizes the structure, content, and practical usage of the data, making it easier to understand and utilize. This approach is designed to be intuitive for data scientists, analysts, and developers, streamlining the experience and minimizing the time required to access and use the data through APIs.

{% if platform == 'socrata' %}
## Data Access (Socrata SODA API)
Data access is facilitated through the **Socrata Open Data API (SODA API)**, part of Tyler Technologies' [Data & Insights platform](https://www.tylertech.com/products/data-insights) (the platform often still referred to as Socrata). These APIs provide robust data discovery and querying capabilities.
* [SODA API Developer Portal](https://dev.socrata.com/)
{% elif platform == 'mtnards' %}
## Data Access (MTNA RDS)
Data access is facilitated through the [**Rich Data Services (RDS)**\(https://www.richdataservices.com) platform API. Designed by [Metadata Technology North America (MTNA)](https://www.mtna.us), RDS provides concurrent access to data and metadata and offers user friendly
interface to datasets stored in back-end SQL databases.
{% endif %}

## Metadata & Enhancements (HVDNet)
To complement the core data APIs, the collection includes supplemental endpoints from the **[High-Value Data Network (HVDNet)](https://www.highvaluedata.net)**. These provide:
* Standards-based, machine-actionable metadata (in formats like Croissant, DCAT, DDI).
* Other specialized services to support the **[FAIR data principles](https://www.go-fair.org/fair-principles/)** (Findable, Accessible, Interoperable, Reusable).

These enhancements simplify data understanding and integration for developers, data scientists, and intelligent agents, significantly reducing data wrangling efforts and boosting productivity.

## Automation
The generation and maintenance of this workspace are automated using the Postman Toolkit and related packages from the **[Data Artifex](https://www.dataartifex.org)** open-source project, ensuring consistency and up-to-date resources.

